Ask HN: Why are all of the user-friendly style transfer apps mobile or web based
text: I was thinking about showing my (mostly non-technical) friend how to play around with image style transfer on their gaming PC and I found that there are plenty of (fantastic) tutorials that involve installing python and pytorch etc., but no simple Windows GUI apps for folks that aren’t super comfortable with a command line. It seems like the tech is mature enough for somebody to have thrown together a way for non-technical people to use it without transmitting their images to the internet.

Ask HN: Where to go for resume advice or HR feedback?
text: Over the past few months I've submitted my resume for product management and software engineering jobs that I feel I'm qualified for. I keep getting rejected before reaching the interview stage.I figure there must be some signals either in my resume or elsewhere that are scaring off employers. I'm in the dark about what I need to change. Is there any HR resource that can give honest feedback?

Clara.io Shutting Down
text:
Received this email today:

Hi Clara User,

This is a notice that we are retiring the Clara product and services on December 31, 2022.

If you have files that you would like to continue using, please download that content before December 31, 2022 because it will not be available after.

We apologize for any inconvenience and thank you for using Clara.

Sincerely,

Clara Admin Team

Ask HN: Is there something like a Casio watch module available as a desktop app?
text:
I was looking for a compact desktop app with alarm, timer, and stopwatch. Then I realized my Casio watches are pretty much ideal for this, but 1) I'm not always wearing one when at the computer and 2) if I want to have 3-4 timers going at once, I could open more than one instance of the app.

Any tips appreciated. Desktop Linux, Wine OK.
